title.narrative: Water and sanitation systems and services are rehabilitated.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF focused on both the provision of life-saving WASH interventions as well as support to the maintenance and/or light emergency rehabilitation of existing WASH systems. 2,969,126 people benefitted from an improved access to water supply and 830,220 from improved access to sanitation while 486,215 people were reached with emergency life-saving WASH services. In addition, UNICEF strengthened the resilience of the sector through the establishment of local chlorine production and the use of solar power in rehabilitated water systems. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:12/01/2022
